Properties cmd args order tests see separate branch
1)use app.setDefaultProperties
.\gradlew bootRun --args="arg1,arg2"
2) .\gradlew bootRun --args="arg1,arg2" -Dprop1=from_cmd
3)use application.properies
.\gradlew bootRun --args="arg1,arg2"

application.properties will override  app.setDefaultProperties but could be overriden -Dprop1
ORDER:
app.setDefaultProperties
application.properties
cmd -D
4)Use prod and dev profiles
.\gradlew bootRun '-Dspring.profiles.active=prod'
.\gradlew bootRun '-Dspring.profiles.active=dev'
.\gradlew bootRun ' will use application.properties
.\gradlew bootRun --args="arg1,arg2" -Dprop1=fromcmd  '-Dspring.profiles.active=prod'
will use cmd

